      "tool": "websearch",
      "code": "{\"query\": \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR root cause analysis fixability 2025 2026\", \"numResults\": 5}",
      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_6718694fafc44b9ba450fb3515493c47\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://techlasi.com/pc/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-12\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\\n\\nBy [MK Usmaan](https://techlasi.com/author/mkusman22/ \\\"View all posts by MK Usmaan\\\") / February 12, 2026\\n\\nAre you facing the dreaded blue screen with a WHEA uncorrectable error message? You’re not alone. This frustrating hardware related error has troubled computer users for years, but with advances in diagnostic technology in 2026, we now have better solutions than ever before. This comprehensive guide will walk you through everything you need to know about WHEA errors, from understanding what they are to implementing the most effective fixes using the latest tools and techniques.\\n\\nWHEA Uncorrectable Error\\n\\n## **What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?**\\n\\nA WHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) uncorrectable error occurs when Windows detects a serious hardware problem that it cannot recover from automatically.\\nUnlike correctable hardware errors that Windows can resolve on the fly, uncorrectable errors force your system to shut down to prevent potential damage to your hardware or data corruption.\\n\\n### **Windows Hardware Error Architecture**\\n\\nWindows Hardware Error Architecture is a platform level error handling mechanism introduced in [Windows Vista](https://techlasi.com/savvy/windows-vs-linux-vs-macos/) that provides a standardized way for the operating system to handle hardware errors. WHEA improves upon the older Machine Check Architecture by offering enhanced error reporting and more detailed diagnostic information.\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n  \\n    + Windows Hardware Error Architecture\\n    + Common Error Codes Associated with WHEA Errors\\n* Primary Causes of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n  \\n    + Hardware Component Failures\\n    + Overclocking Issues\\n    + Driver and Firmware Problems\\n* Symptoms and Identification of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n+ Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) Appearances\\n    + Event Viewer Diagnostics\\n* Step-by-Step Troubleshooting Guide\\n  \\n    + Immediate Actions to Take\\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Procedures\\n    + Hardware Component Verification\\n* Prevention Strategies for WHEA Errors\\n  \\n    + Proper System Maintenance\\n    + Cooling Solutions and Temperature Management\\n    + Safe Overclocking Practices\\n* Recent Developments in WHEA Error Management\\n  \\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Tools\\n    + AI Assisted Troubleshooting\\n* Conclusion\\n* FAQs\\n  \\n    + Can software cause WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + How can I tell which hardware component is causing my WHEA error?\\n    + Are WHEA errors covered under warranty?\\n    + Can updating BIOS fix WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + Why do WHEA errors sometimes occur only during specific activities like gaming?\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://mdrepairs.com/blog/whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error Fix | Windows Blue Screen\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-04-08\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"This is one of several blue screen errors that can indicate storage problems. The good news is that some causes are fixable with basic troubleshooting. Overheating, outdated drivers, bad BIOS settings. The bad news? If the error keeps coming back, you’re probably looking at a hardware failure. And if your storage drive is the culprit, your data could be at risk.\\n\\nWe see computers with this error come through our data recovery lab regularly. Sometimes it’s a simple overheating issue and the customer fixes it by cleaning out dust. Other times, the drive has bad sectors spreading across the platters, and recovery is the only way to save the files. The key is figuring out which situation you’re in before you lose anything important.\\n\\nIf you’re getting this blue screen repeatedly and you’re worried about your data, our data recovery team can evaluate your drive for free. No obligation, just answers.\\n\\n### What’s in This Guide\\n\\n* What Is the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n* Common Causes of This Blue Screen\\n* Step-by-Step Fixes (Start Here)\\n* Advanced Fixes for Persistent Errors\\n* When WHEA Points to a Dying Drive\\n* Protecting Your Data During WHEA Errors\\n* When You Need Professional Data Recovery\\n* Frequently Asked Questions\\n\\n## What Is the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n\\nWHEA is a system built into Windows (Vista and later) that monitors hardware components for errors. Your CPU, memory controller, PCIe bus, and storage controllers all report errors through WHEA. Most of the time, WHEA catches and corrects small errors silently in the background. You never even notice.\\n\\nThe blue screen happens when WHEA encounters an error it **cannot** correct. Something has gone wrong at the hardware level, and Windows decides the safest thing to do is stop everything immediately rather than risk data corruption or further damage. That’s what “uncorrectable” means. Windows tried to fix it, failed, and pulled the emergency brake.\\n\\nThe stop code is **0x00000124** .\\nYou’ll usually see it displayed on the blue screen itself, along with the text WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR. Windows 10 and 11 show a sad face emoji and the stop code. Older versions show the classic wall of white text on blue.\\n\\n**Quick context:** Not every blue screen means hardware failure. Driver crashes, software conflicts, and Windows Update bugs cause blue screens too. But WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR specifically indicates a _hardware_ error. That’s what makes it more serious than your average BSOD.\\n\\n### What Windows Is Actually Telling You\\n\\nWhen you get this BSOD, Windows creates a memory dump file with details about the error: which component failed, the error type, and sometimes a specific error code. Most people never look at these dumps. But tools like [WinDbg from Microsoft](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/debugger/) or the free BlueScreenView utility can parse them and tell you \"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.positioniseverything.net/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide-for-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-05-17\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"+ [CPU](https://www.positioniseverything.net/category/hardware/cpu/)\\n  \\n    + [Outlook](https://www.positioniseverything.net/category/microsoft-office/outlook/)\\n    + [Powerpoint](https://www.positioniseverything.net/category/microsoft-office/powerpoint/)\\n\\nSearch for:\\n\\nCategory [Blog](https://www.positioniseverything.net/category/blog/)\\n\\n# WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\\n\\nBy [positioniseverything](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/) Published May 17, 2026 21 min read\\n\\n* Author\\n* Recent Posts\\n\\n[](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/ \\\"positioniseverything\\\")\\n\\n[positioniseverything](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/)\\n\\n[](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/ \\\"positioniseverything\\\")\\n\\nLatest posts by positioniseverything ( [see all](https://www.positioniseverything.net/author/positioniseverything/) )\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error is one of the more serious Windows blue screen errors because it usually points to a low-level hardware, firmware, or driver problem rather than a simple app crash. It can appear during gaming, startup, heavy workloads, Windows updates, or even while the PC is idle, often with little warning beyond a sudden restart and a stop code.\\n\\nIn 2026, the safest way to handle this error is to diagnose it methodically: check temperatures and power stability, remove unstable overclocks, test RAM and storage, review CPU and GPU behavior, update drivers, and verify BIOS/UEFI settings before replacing parts. A careful approach helps separate a temporary configuration issue from signs of failing hardware.\\n\\n[Guide Helped? Tip Us](https://ko-fi.com/yorkermedia) ×\\n\\n|\\\\# |Preview |Product |Price | |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n|1 |[Anker USB C Hub, 7in1 Multi-Port USB Adapter for Laptop/Mac, 4K@60Hz USB C to HDMI Splitter, 85W Max PD, 2 USB 3.\\n0 & 1 USBC Data Ports, SD/TF Card Reader, for Type C Devices (Charger Not Included)](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DXJQT19B?tag=positioniseverything-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=usb+c+accessories \\\"Anker USB C Hub, 7in1 Multi-Port USB Adapter for Laptop/Mac, 4K@60Hz USB C to HDMI Splitter, 85W Max PD, 2 USB 3.0 & 1 USBC Data Ports, SD/TF Card Reader, for Type C Devices (Charger Not Included)\\\") |[Anker USB C Hub, 7in1 Multi-Port USB Adapter for Laptop/Mac, 4K@60Hz USB C to HDMI Splitter, 85W Max...](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DXJQT19B?tag=positioniseverything-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=usb+c+accessories \\\"Anker USB C Hub, 7in1 Multi-Port USB Adapter for Laptop/Mac, 4K@60Hz USB C to HDMI Splitter, 85W Max PD, 2 USB 3.0 & 1 USBC Data Ports, SD/TF Card Reader, for Type C Devices (Charger Not Included)\\\") |$25.99 |[Buy on Amazon](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DXJQT19B?tag=positioniseverything-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=usb+c+accessories \\\"Buy on Amazo\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://umatechnology.org/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide-for-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Check the drive’s SMART health with the manufacturer’s tool, update SSD firmware, reseat the drive if it is removable, and make sure it has adequate cooling. Back up files immediately if the drive reports media errors, critical warnings, or rapid health decline.\\n\\n### Should I update my BIOS or UEFI to fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nA BIOS/UEFI update can help if the problem is related to CPU microcode, memory compatibility, PCIe stability, or a newer processor installed on an older motherboard. Use the motherboard or laptop manufacturer’s exact model page, avoid beta firmware unless support recommends it, and do not interrupt the update. After updating, load optimized defaults before reapplying settings such as XMP, EXPO, undervolting, or fan curves.\\n\\n### Is it safe to keep using a PC that gets WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nOccasional crashes after a bad driver or unstable tuning may not mean immediate hardware failure, but repeated WHEA errors should not be ignored.\\nContinued use can risk data loss if the cause is storage failure, overheating, or unstable power. Back up your data first, remove overclocks, monitor temperatures, and stop heavy workloads until the system passes stability tests.\\n\\n## Bottom Line\\n\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error is usually a sign that Windows detected a serious hardware or low-level system stability problem, so the safest approach is to troubleshoot methodically: undo recent changes, check temperatures, update BIOS/UEFI and drivers, then test memory, storage, CPU, GPU, and power stability.\\n\\nIf the error continues after clean updates, safe settings, and component diagnostics, treat it as a likely failing part rather than a normal software crash. Back up data, stop overclocking, and consider professional testing or hardware replacement before the issue leads to data loss or an unbootable system.\\n\\n#### Quick Recap\\n\\nBestseller No. 1\\n\\n[Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.\\n1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09TL7K1TF?tag=umatechnology09-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=windows+recovery+software \\\"Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more\\\")\\n\\n[Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09TL7K1TF?tag=umatechnology09-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=windows+recovery+software \\\"Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more\\\")\\n\\nData recovery software for retrieving lost files; Easily recover documents, audios, videos, photos, images and \"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ninjaone.com/blog/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-in-windows-11\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix \\\"WHEA_Uncorrectable_Error\\\" in Windows 11\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-24\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Home / Blog / IT Ops / How to Fix the WHEA\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error in Windows 11\\n\\nIT Ops\\n\\n/\\n\\n* Last updated February 24, 2026\\n\\n/\\n\\n* 6 min read\\n\\n# How to Fix the WHEA\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error in Windows 11\\n\\n* Picture of Mikhail Blacer Mikhail Blacer\\n\\nby Mikhail Blacer , IT Technical Writer\\n\\nHow to Fix the WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 11 blog banner image\\n\\nTable of contents\\n\\n## Instant Summary\\n\\nSummarize Blog\\n\\nThis NinjaOne blog post offers a comprehensive basic CMD commands list and deep dive into Windows commands with over 70 essential cmd commands for both beginners and advanced users. It explains practical command prompt commands for file management, directory navigation, network troubleshooting, disk operations, and automation with real examples to improve productivity. Whether you’re learning foundational cmd commands or mastering advanced Windows CLI tools, this guide helps you use the Command Prompt more effectively.\\n\\nFree Trial\\n\\n## Key Points\\n* Identify Faulting Hardware: Review WHEA-Logger events in Event Viewer to isolate CPU, memory, PCIe bus, or storage errors.\\n* Update BIOS/UEFI Firmware First: Install vendor-supported firmware updates to fix instability from outdated microcode, voltage control, or PCIe initialization.\\n* Run Targeted Hardware Diagnostics: Stress-test RAM, CPU, and storage using vendor tools or industry-standard diagnostics to confirm whether components fail under load.\\n* Update Chipset, Storage, and Device Drivers: Install the latest supported drivers to correct hardware signaling issues that may trigger repeated WHEA events.\\n* Validate Post-Repair Stability: Clear WHEA logs, apply stress tests, and monitor Event Viewer to ensure the system remains stable without recurring hardware faults.\\n\\nA WHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) Uncorrectable Error (or **whea\\\\_uncorrectable\\\\_error** ) occurs when hardware reports a fault via the WHEA system.\\nIt’s known as a blue screen of death (BSOD) error that comes from failing CPUs, unstable memory, PCIe bus issues, storage faults, or outdated firmware.\\n\\nThis guide delivers a workflow to fix a WHEA Uncorrectable Error. We’ll go through ways on how to identify the hardware source, run targeted diagnostics, update firmware, remove overclocking, and verify system stability.\\n\\n## Steps to fix the WHEA uncorrectable error\\n\\nTo stop the [WHEA uncorrectable error code](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/whea/introduction-to-the-windows-hardware-error-architecture) , you will need to perform hardware-focused troubleshooting. Before you go through the steps, you will need to confirm the following requirements:\\n\\n📌 **Prerequisites:**\\n\\n* You will need administrator access on the affected device.\\n* This requires you to enter BIOS or UEFI for firmware and stability changes.\\n* You will need to have tools for memory, CPU, and storage diagnostics.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.windowsmode.com/fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-windows\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR in Windows 10/11\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Most people solve it by Fix 2 or Fix 3. If your PC is overclocked, start with Fix 1 first.\\n\\nWhat This Error Means at a Glance\\n\\n* Windows detected an unrecoverable hardware error and forced a restart.\\n* Most common causes: overclocking, faulty RAM, bad device driver, or overheating CPU.\\n* Less common causes: failing hard drive or SSD, corrupted system files, bad Windows update.\\n* This is a hardware-level crash, not a typical app or software error.\\n* Affects Windows 10 and Windows 11. More common on overclocked or custom-built PCs.\\n\\nError Type\\n\\nBSOD / Hardware\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n\\nCPU / RAM / Driver\\n\\nAffects\\n\\nWindows 10 / 11\\n\\nDifficulty\\n\\nBeginner to advanced\\n\\nTime to Fix\\n\\n10 min – several hours\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* Video: How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR on Windows\\n* What Causes WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n* How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n* Quick Checklist: What to Try First\\n* Still Getting WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR? Advanced Steps\\n* Frequently Asked Questions\\n* Related Windows Error Fixes\\n\\n## Video: How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR on Windows\\n\\nWatch the full fix walkthrough for WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR on Windows 10 and 11, covering the overclocking reset, driver update, RAM test, and SFC repair steps shown below.\\n\\n## What Causes WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n\\nThis error has more possible causes than most blue screens. Check the list below and pick the fix that best matches your situation before working through the numbered steps.\\n\\nOverclocking (Most Common)\\n\\nRunning your CPU, RAM, or GPU faster than stock speeds puts extra stress on the hardware. Even a previously stable overclock can cause this error after a Windows update, temperature spike, or power fluctuation.\\n\\nFaulty or Incompatible RAM\\n\\nBad memory is one of the top hardware causes. This includes physically failing RAM sticks, RAM running at the wrong speed for your motherboard, or mismatched sticks that are not compatible with each other.\\n\\nBad or Outdated Drivers\\nGPU drivers, chipset drivers, and storage controller drivers are the most common driver culprits. A buggy driver update can trigger this error even on hardware that was working fine the day before.\\n\\nOverheating CPU or GPU\\n\\nWhen a processor gets too hot, it can trigger hardware-level errors that cause this blue screen. Common on laptops with blocked vents, desktops with dried-out thermal paste, or rigs running demanding workloads in a hot room.\\n\\nFailing Hard Drive or SSD\\n\\nA drive that is starting to fail can trigger hardware errors as Windows tries to read or write to bad sectors. This is more common on older HDDs but can also happen with SSDs that are near end of life.\\n\\nCorrupted System Files\\n\\nA failed Windows update, a sudden shutdown during an update, or malware can corrupt core Windows files. This is less common than hardware causes but worth checking if all hardware tests come back clean.\\n\\n## How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRE\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://couldask.com/en/guides/tech/oswindows/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 10/11 — Step-by-Step Guide\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-06-27\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Sunday, June 28\\n\\nTheme\\n\\nEN ▾\\n\\n[Русский](https://couldask.com/ru/kak-ispravit-oshibku-whea-uncorrectable-error) [English](https://couldask.com/en/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error)\\n\\n🏠 Home Sections: All 📖 Guides 🔧 Fixes 💡 Concepts ⚖️ Compare 🛠️ Tools Справка\\n\\n×\\n\\n#### Help\\n\\nUse the search bar to find error codes or manuals. Articles are categorized in the top menu.\\n\\nSubcategories: Back All Adults Contact Excel Git Google Mail Media Windows More 7 ▾\\n\\n### Select Subcategory\\n\\n×\\n\\nHome / Guides / IT & Tech / Windows\\n\\nIT & Tech\\n\\n# How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 10/11\\n\\nCouldAsk Editorial 27\\\\.06.2026 2 min 👁️ 139\\n\\nQuick Solution\\n\\nError 0x00000124 is a critical hardware failure (overheating, overclocking, or power issues). Key steps: reset BIOS to factory defaults, disable overclocking, and check system files and disk integrity.\\nBlue screen of death with WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR and stop code 0x00000124 on a computer monitor The **WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR** (stop code `0x00000124` ) is a critical failure of the Windows Hardware Error Architecture. Unlike many other Blue Screen of Death (BSoD) errors, this one indicates a hardware issue in 90% of cases, rather than a software glitch.\\n\\n## Main Causes of the Error\\n\\nThe system protects itself to prevent physical damage to the components. The primary culprits are:\\n\\n* Overheating of the processor (CPU) or graphics card (GPU).\\n* Unstable overclocking or enabled XMP profiles for RAM.\\n* A faulty power supply unit (PSU) causing voltage spikes.\\n* Physical wear and tear of the system drive (SSD/HDD).\\n\\n## Step-by-Step Solution\\n\\n### Step 1: Disable Overclocking\\n\\nIf you have overclocked your CPU or RAM, revert to the base settings.\\n1\\\\. Restart your computer and enter the BIOS/UEFI (usually by pressing `Del` or `F2` ).\\n2\\\\.\\nFind the **Load Optimized Defaults** option or manually reset the CPU and RAM frequency settings (disable XMP).\\n3\\\\. Save the changes ( `F10` ) and reboot.\\n\\n⚠️ Before updating or resetting the BIOS, ensure your computer is connected to a reliable power source (ideally through a UPS). A sudden power outage while working in the BIOS can brick your motherboard.\\n\\n### Step 2: Check System Files and Disk\\n\\nIf the BIOS is reset but the error persists, check the integrity of the file system.\\nOpen the Command Prompt as an Administrator and type the following commands one by one:\\n\\n* `chkdsk /f /r` (requires a reboot to scan the disk).\\n* `sfc /scannow` (system file check).\\n\\nℹ️ Pro Tip\\n\\nThe WHEA error often occurs after installing new RAM sticks. If you recently upgraded your memory, try removing the modules, wiping the contacts with a regular eraser, and pushing them back in until you hear a distinct click.\\n\\n## Recommended Reading\\n\\nFor an in-depth analysis of BSoD causes, I recommend studying:\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"Whea Uncorrectable Error - Troubleshooting\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2022-06-29\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"com%2Ftopic%2F1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error%2F%3Fdo%3DfindComment%26comment%3D15459738&title=Whea+Uncorrectable+Error \\\"Share on Reddit\\\")\\n\\n* * *\\n\\nMore sharing options...\\n\\n- [](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/ \\\"Go to Windows7ge's profile\\\") [](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/badges/)\\n* ### **[Windows7ge](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/ \\\"Go to Windows7ge's profile\\\")**\\n* Member\\n* Writer of Guides & Tutorials\\n    + [12\\\\.3k](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/content/ \\\"12,308 posts\\\")\\n    + [255](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/solutions/ \\\"255 solutions\\\")\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=4773) [](https://www.boincstats.com/stats/-1/user/detail/73865194514/overview)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7093)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?\\napp=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7229) [](https://folding.extremeoverclocking.com/user_summary.php?s=&u=1294415)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7560)\\n\\n[Posted June 29, 2022](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error/?do=findComment&comment=15459750)\\n\\n* [](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error/ \\\"Share this post\\\")\\n\\nUsually WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is associated with a hardware failure. This could be an issue with your PSU, GPU, Motherboard, etc.\\n\\nJust from my experience dealing with this error in the past I'd try a different PSU first but you can try pulling sticks of RAM if you want to test something easier. I wouldn't put my trust in whatever Windows memory check is. Most people use MemTestx86 for memory testing and even then there's no guarantee the memory error will propagate on the first go around.\\nMultiple runs might be required so I'll often just pull a stick at a time and see if the system becomes stable again. Faster. Just as easy.\\n\\n**Guides & Tutorials:**\\n\\n[PROXMOX - Rebuilding ZFS RAID rpool After Disk Failure](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1535985-proxmox-rebuilding-zfs-raid-rpool-after-disk-failure/)\\n\\n[Mass Deploying Customized Windows 10/11 Installs](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1531766-mass-deploying-customized-windows-1011-installs/)\\n\\n[Building a GNU/Linux Based Windows Deployment Server](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1482112-building-a-gnulinux-based-windows-deployment-server/)\\n\\n[GNU/Linux Installer Server: Installation & Configuration](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1445036-gnulinux-installer-server-installation-configuration/)\\n\\n[How to: Use (i)PXE to Install Windows from a Network](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1441143-how-to-use-ipxe-to-install-windows-from-a-network/)\\n\\n[Why Memorize IP's When You Can Self-Host DNS Instead?\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/techsupport/comments/swor16/whea_uncorrectable_error_without_any_obvious_way\",\n      \"title\": \"whea uncorrectable error without any obvious way to fix\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"whea uncorrectable error without any obvious way to fix\\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR is often caused by failing NVMe SSDs. Use the instruction here to show the parameter values on the blue screen. If the\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-7c49d78a-2792-96cf-2268-abbe9d9eb29f\",\n      \"title\": \"How to fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR - Microsoft Support\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Skip to main content\\n\\n[Microsoft](https://www.microsoft.com)\\n\\nSupport\\n\\n[Support](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us)\\n\\nSupport\\n\\nSearch Search for help\\n\\n* No results Cancel\\n\\nSign in or create an account.\\n\\nHello,\\n\\nSelect a different account.\\n\\nYou have multiple accounts\\n\\nChoose the account you want to sign in with.\\n\\nRelated topics\\n\\n# How to fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\nApplies To\\n\\nWindows 11 Windows 10\\n\\nWhen a hardware error occurs on a Windows device, it shuts down suddenly and might display a blue screen/stop error with the following error message:\\n\\n**WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR**\\n\\nTo attempt to fix this issue, try the actions from the following list:\\n\\n## Use Windows Update to receive the latest updates and drivers\\n\\nUse Windows Update to receive the latest updates and drivers. For more information on how to use Windows Update to receive the latest updates and drivers, see the following article:\\n\\nAutomatically get recommended drivers and updates for your hardware\\n## Manually update drivers\\n\\nIf the blue screen/stop error gives an indication of which hardware device is causing the issue, the drivers for the hardware device causing the issue can be manually updated. For more information, see the following article:\\n\\nUpdate drivers through Device Manager in Windows\\n\\n**Important:** Microsoft recommends trying to first automatically update drivers using Windows Update. For more information, see the article Automatically get recommended drivers and updates for your hardware .\\n\\n## Use System Restore or Startup Repair\\n\\nUse one of the Windows options to restore or repair Windows. This option is the best option when a recent change was done to the Windows device that could be causing the issue, for example:\\n\\n* Microsoft updates were installed.\\n* An updated driver was installed.\\n* A new app was installed.\\n\\nFor more information, see the following article:\\n\\nRecovery options in Windows\\n\\n## Troubleshoot the blue screen/stop error\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0d4356d58ffe6WA0D4tWZ5oZRG\"\n}",
